quran[19]{c,v,t,f}:
  79,46,"The Day they see it, (it will be) as if they had not tarried (in this world) except an afternoon or a morning."
  83,31,"And when they returned to their own people, they would return jesting;"
  83,32,"And when they saw them, they said: "
  83,33,"But they (disbelievers, sinners) had not been sent as watchers over them (the believers)."
  87,16,"Nay, you prefer the life of this world,"
  87,17,"Although the Hereafter is better and more lasting."
  87,18,"Verily, this is in the former Scriptures -"
  88,13,"Therein will be thrones raised high."
  88,14,"And cups set at hand."
  88,15,"And cushions set in rows."
  89,10,"And (with) Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) who had the stakes (to torture men by binding them to the stakes)?"
  89,11,"Who did transgress beyond bounds in the lands (in the disobedience of Allâh)."
  89,12,"And made therein much mischief."
  90,4,"Verily, We have created man in toil."
  90,5,"Does he think that none can overcome him?"
  90,6,"He says (boastfully): "
  91,1,"By the sun and its brightness."
  91,2,"By the moon as it follows it (the sun)."
  91,3,"By the day as it shows up (the sun’s) brightness."